# ── Vendored heavyweight tooling (not redistributed; see README §3 + docs/) ──
# .venv/  = in-repo Python venv (numpy/scipy/matplotlib/pillow)
# .tools/ = vendored Godot 4.6.3 binary
# .vendor/ = EZ-RASSOR source checkout (incl. unlicensed extra_models/)
.venv/
.tools/
.vendor/

# ── Godot editor cache + import sidecars ──
godot_sidecar/.godot/
*.import

# ── Python bytecode + packaging build artifacts ──
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# ── Third-party copyrighted research PDFs — NOT redistributed ──
# Journal / IEEE / NASA / conference papers: John's private research library,
# cited by filename throughout the repo (README §4, scene metadata) but cannot be
# relicensed CC0 or redistributed. See papers/CITATIONS.md for the reference list.
# Same exclusion rationale as .vendor/extra_models (THIRD_PARTY.md).
papers/*
!papers/CITATIONS.md

# ── crater_caveins raw time series (~110 MB, regenerable) ──
# 102-frame float32 raster sequence, deterministically rebuilt by
# `python -m terrain_authority.scenes` (build_crater_caveins, seed=5).
# Commit only the bookend frames (t000, t101) + previews; the motion is already
# captured by viz/out/caveins.gif and caveins_filmstrip.png.
samples/crater_caveins/t*/
!samples/crater_caveins/t000/
!samples/crater_caveins/t101/

# ── tread_track raw time series (~35 MB, regenerable) ──
# 32-frame float32 raster sequence, deterministically rebuilt by
# `python -m terrain_authority.scenes` (build_tread_track, seed=11).
# Commit only the bookend frames (t000, t031) + previews; the motion is already
# captured by viz/out/tread_track.gif and tread_track_filmstrip.png.
samples/tread_track/t*/
!samples/tread_track/t000/
!samples/tread_track/t031/

# ── tread_track_4wheel raw time series (regenerable) ──
# 19-frame 4-wheel drive, deterministically rebuilt by `python -m terrain_authority.scenes`
# (build_tread_track_4wheel, seed=11). Commit only the bookends: t000 (pristine) + t018
# (final, carrying the per-frame §5.2 wheel_tracks metadata + the §5.3 tiles[] descriptors).
# Motion frames t001..t017 AND the 164 fine 1 cm tile RASTERS under t018/tiles/ are regenerable
# (~4.5 MB / 984 files) — gitignored like the other raster sequences; t018/metadata.json still
# documents every tile (id/region_rc/cell_m/dir), so the variable-resolution contract is captured.
samples/tread_track_4wheel/t*/
!samples/tread_track_4wheel/t000/
!samples/tread_track_4wheel/t018/
samples/tread_track_4wheel/t018/tiles/
# (excavation_marks is only 2 frames — committed in full, not ignored.)

# ── tread_track_4wheel_1cm fly-through SHOWCASE raw frames (regenerable) ──
# 25-frame global-1 cm drive (512x512 @ 0.01 m = 5.12 m), rebuilt by
# scripts/build_flythrough_1cm.py. Commit only the bookends t000 (pristine) + t024 (final);
# the motion frames (~125 MB of 512^2 rasters) are regenerable.
samples/tread_track_4wheel_1cm/t*/
!samples/tread_track_4wheel_1cm/t000/
!samples/tread_track_4wheel_1cm/t024/

# ── Godot fly-through frame PNGs (regenerable) ──
# The numbered per-frame renders from `sidecar.gd --sequence`; deterministically rebuilt by
# `render.sh -- --sequence ...`. Commit only the assembled quadtree_flythrough.gif (the
# deliverable); the individual frames are heavy at 1080p and regenerable.
godot_sidecar/out/quadtree_flythrough_*.png

# ── M0 multi-camera feasibility-probe outputs (scratch, regenerable) ──
# Per-camera frames + contact sheet from `sidecar.gd --probe-multicam`; the probe just proves
# multi-SubViewport headless capture works, so its PNGs are scratch (rebuild with the flag).
godot_sidecar/out/probe_cam_*.png
godot_sidecar/out/probe_multicam_sheet.png

# ── M1 front-stereo camera egress (render output, regenerable) ──
# `sidecar.gd --cameras` writes out/cam/<scene>/<NNN>/{front_left,front_right}.png + sensors.json
# (sensor_bridge_contract §2.1, "under godot_sidecar/out/, git-ignored"). All regenerable from the
# committed .gd source; sensors.json + PNGs are render output, NOT committed.
godot_sidecar/out/cam/

# ── Wave-2a lane render egress (regenerable; res:// = godot_sidecar/) ──
# A2-sweep --sun-sweep -> out/sun_sweep/<scene>/{manifest.json,NNN.png};
# M3-tag --lander-faces -> out/lander_faces/<scene>/{face PNGs, sensors.json}.
godot_sidecar/out/sun_sweep/
godot_sidecar/out/lander_faces/

# ── detour: stereo staging for the ROS depth/fiducial outputs (scratch, regenerable) ──
# `out/detour/<name>/` holds the staged stereo pairs + sensors.json fed to depth_map.py /
# fiducial_overlay.py; the committed deliverables live in out/ros/. Also the working hero render.
godot_sidecar/out/detour/
godot_sidecar/out/crater_drop_hero.png
godot_sidecar/out/grit_check.png
godot_sidecar/out/grit_check_grey.png
godot_sidecar/out/grit_tread.png
godot_sidecar/out/rover_worn.png
godot_sidecar/out/clast_grey_check.png

# ── Wave-1 lane scratch at repo-root out/ (regenerable; only godot_sidecar/out/ was covered) ──
# COLMAP SfM/MVS staging (views + sparse/dense model + trajectory JSON), multi-frame stereo
# egress smoke dirs, and sun-sweep frames. The committed deliverables live elsewhere; these are
# rebuilt by scripts/colmap/colmap_recon.py, --cameras-seq, and --sun-sweep respectively.
/out/colmap/
/out/cam/
/out/sun_sweep/
/out/_smoke/

# ── Spiral-demo render egress + built scene (regenerable) ──
# build_spiral_scene.py deterministically rebuilds out/scenes/<name> (seed=1234); the per-frame
# spiral renders ride out/cam/ (already ignored above). demo_lit/ + demo_unlit/ are demo_spiral.py
# report output (telemetry/summary JSON + plots), and brdf_*/crater_boulders_{hapke,lambert} are
# lit-vs-Lambert comparison scratch -- all regenerable from the committed .gd + scripts/demo/.
# The curated viz-battery GIFs in out/panels/ ARE the committed deliverable (cf. quadtree_flythrough.gif).
godot_sidecar/out/scenes/
godot_sidecar/out/demo_lit/
godot_sidecar/out/demo_unlit/
godot_sidecar/out/brdf_compare_*.png
godot_sidecar/out/brdf_demo_*.png
godot_sidecar/out/crater_boulders_hapke.png
godot_sidecar/out/crater_boulders_lambert.png

# ── WorkSite streaming roam (scripts/demo/worksite_*.py). The curated 3x2 composite + GIFs +
#    telemetry ARE committed deliverables; the per-step frames, paged tiles, render bundles, and
#    npz are regenerable scratch (worksite_roam.py + worksite_progress.py rebuild them). ──
/out/worksite_roam/frames/
/out/worksite_roam/tiles_page/
/out/worksite_roam/berm_scene/
/out/worksite_roam/berm_scene_local/
/out/worksite_roam/corridor.npz
/out/worksite_roam/godot_cmd.txt
/out/worksite_slice/tiles_page/
/out/worksite_slice/fine_scene/
